<div id="review_23214744" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/23214744" />
    <a title="Maggie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/963509-maggie"><img alt="Maggie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1204742322p2/963509.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/23214744?book_show_action=true">May 29, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maggie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maggie" href="/user/show/963509-maggie">Maggie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer23214744" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8813490601134697093">This should be required reading for anyone living in the west and for all politicians. The author does a fine job of telling the story of the Dust Bowl era, why it happened (natural forces and human actions), and where we stand today. It&apos;s clear to see that adding climate change to the mix requires us to develop stronger conservation policies &amp; practices if we want to avoid such a catastrophe happening again. With the population we have in this area now, I can&apos;t imagine the suffering or how we w</span>
  <span id="freeText8813490601134697093" style="display:none">This should be required reading for anyone living in the west and for all politicians. The author does a fine job of telling the story of the Dust Bowl era, why it happened (natural forces and human actions), and where we stand today. It's clear to see that adding climate change to the mix requires us to develop stronger conservation policies &amp; practices if we want to avoid such a catastrophe happening again. With the population we have in this area now, I can't imagine the suffering or how we would recover. The old photographs included in this book are truly worth a thousand words!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8813490601134697093" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

